<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>No-Matches on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/no-matches/</link><description>Recent content in No-Matches on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/no-matches/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Bash No Matches Found Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/no-matching/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/no-matching/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="bash-no-matches-found-error-fix"&gt;Bash No Matches Found Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when a glob pattern (wildcard) doesn&amp;rsquo;t match any files or directories, and &lt;code&gt;failglob&lt;/code&gt; is set.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bash expands glob patterns like &lt;code&gt;*.txt&lt;/code&gt; into matching filenames. By default, if no match exists, the pattern is passed as a literal string. With &lt;code&gt;shopt -s failglob&lt;/code&gt;, Bash errors instead. This can also appear in zsh (where it&amp;rsquo;s the default behavior).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pattern doesn&amp;rsquo;t match anything&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;*.xyz&lt;/code&gt; when no &lt;code&gt;.xyz&lt;/code&gt; files exist.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wrong directory&lt;/strong&gt; — globbing in a directory that doesn&amp;rsquo;t contain the expected files.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;zsh default behavior&lt;/strong&gt; — zsh errors on unmatched globs by default.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Case sensitivity&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;*.TXT&lt;/code&gt; won&amp;rsquo;t match &lt;code&gt;file.txt&lt;/code&gt; on case-sensitive systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-if-files-exist-before-globbing"&gt;Fix 1: Check if files exist before globbing&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;shopt -s nullglob
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;files&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=(&lt;/span&gt;*.txt&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[[&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;${#&lt;/span&gt;files[@]&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; -gt &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]]&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; f in &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;files[@]&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$f&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;done&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fi&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-disable-failglob-if-you-want-the-pattern-as-literal"&gt;Fix 2: Disable failglob if you want the pattern as literal&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;shopt -u failglob
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo *.txt &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# outputs &amp;#34;*.txt&amp;#34; if no match&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-verify-the-current-directory"&gt;Fix 3: Verify the current directory&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pwd
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ls -la
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Confirm you&amp;#39;re where you expect to be&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-a-conditional-check-in-zsh"&gt;Fix 4: Use a conditional check in zsh&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# In zsh, use (N) glob qualifier for nullglob behavior&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;files&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=(&lt;/span&gt;*.txt&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;N&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;))&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;((&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;${#&lt;/span&gt;files&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;))&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;files[@]&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fi&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ shopt -s failglob
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ echo *.xyz
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;bash: no matches found: *.xyz
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ ls *.log
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;zsh: no matches found: *.log
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ echo *.txt
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;*.txt
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# (without failglob, pattern is passed literally)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="glob-expand"&gt;Glob Expansion Error&lt;/a&gt; — unexpected glob behavior.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="no-such-file"&gt;No Such File or Directory&lt;/a&gt; — specific file reference doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>